WEBVTT

00:00:20.116 --> 00:00:22.856 A:middle
&gt;&gt; Good morning, and welcome to

00:00:22.856 --> 00:00:24.306 A:middle
Debugging with Xcode 9.

00:00:25.296 --> 00:00:26.826 A:middle
I'm Chris Miles and I work on

00:00:26.906 --> 00:00:27.386 A:middle
Xcode.

00:00:27.906 --> 00:00:29.056 A:middle
We've got a lot of great new

00:00:29.056 --> 00:00:30.526 A:middle
debugging features to talk about

00:00:30.526 --> 00:00:32.036 A:middle
today, so let's dive straight

00:00:32.036 --> 00:00:33.026 A:middle
into it.

00:00:33.666 --> 00:00:35.746 A:middle
I'd like to start by talking

00:00:35.746 --> 00:00:37.646 A:middle
about developing and debugging

00:00:37.646 --> 00:00:38.346 A:middle
with devices.

00:00:39.146 --> 00:00:40.626 A:middle
Let's take a look at our typical

00:00:40.626 --> 00:00:41.696 A:middle
development configuration.

00:00:42.716 --> 00:00:44.046 A:middle
We've got our Mac running Xcode

00:00:44.046 --> 00:00:45.966 A:middle
and nearby we have the device

00:00:45.966 --> 00:00:46.956 A:middle
that we're developing with.

00:00:47.656 --> 00:00:49.556 A:middle
Connecting the two we have the

00:00:49.556 --> 00:00:50.826 A:middle
familiar white cable.

00:00:50.826 --> 00:00:53.206 A:middle
Now, this configuration has

00:00:53.206 --> 00:00:55.006 A:middle
suited us very well for almost

00:00:55.006 --> 00:00:57.026 A:middle
ten years now, but more and more

00:00:57.026 --> 00:00:58.776 A:middle
developers are finding needs to

00:00:58.776 --> 00:01:01.236 A:middle
be more mobile while debugging

00:01:01.356 --> 00:01:03.696 A:middle
with their devices, and to make

00:01:03.736 --> 00:01:05.196 A:middle
this easier, I'm proud to

00:01:05.196 --> 00:01:07.736 A:middle
announce that with Xcode 9 that

00:01:07.736 --> 00:01:08.976 A:middle
white cable is no longer needed.

00:01:09.516 --> 00:01:15.316 A:middle
[ Applause ]

00:01:15.816 --> 00:01:17.366 A:middle
It is now possible to develop

00:01:17.366 --> 00:01:18.896 A:middle
and debug on your device over

00:01:18.896 --> 00:01:21.166 A:middle
Wi-Fi, and we call this wireless

00:01:21.166 --> 00:01:21.746 A:middle
development.

00:01:21.746 --> 00:01:25.736 A:middle
So who can take advantage of

00:01:25.736 --> 00:01:26.696 A:middle
wireless development?

00:01:27.346 --> 00:01:28.506 A:middle
Well, we think many developers

00:01:28.506 --> 00:01:29.686 A:middle
are going to love it, but here

00:01:29.686 --> 00:01:31.106 A:middle
are some obvious examples.

00:01:31.786 --> 00:01:34.076 A:middle
With the introduction of ARKit

00:01:34.426 --> 00:01:36.156 A:middle
this week, I'm sure many of you

00:01:36.156 --> 00:01:38.316 A:middle
are eager to sit down and build

00:01:38.316 --> 00:01:40.626 A:middle
an augmented reality app.

00:01:42.416 --> 00:01:44.226 A:middle
While debugging your app you're

00:01:44.226 --> 00:01:45.196 A:middle
going to need to be moving

00:01:45.196 --> 00:01:46.366 A:middle
around more than you might be

00:01:46.366 --> 00:01:47.976 A:middle
used to, holding your phone,

00:01:48.336 --> 00:01:49.516 A:middle
doing this kind of thing, and

00:01:49.886 --> 00:01:51.226 A:middle
being able to get away from the

00:01:51.226 --> 00:01:52.436 A:middle
computer to do this will make

00:01:52.436 --> 00:01:53.796 A:middle
that much easier than it

00:01:53.796 --> 00:01:55.406 A:middle
otherwise would have been.

00:01:56.416 --> 00:01:57.456 A:middle
For those of you building

00:01:57.456 --> 00:01:59.406 A:middle
fitness apps, you probably know

00:01:59.406 --> 00:02:01.156 A:middle
that the best way to test and

00:02:01.156 --> 00:02:02.336 A:middle
debug your fitness app is for

00:02:02.336 --> 00:02:03.616 A:middle
the athlete to wear the device

00:02:03.676 --> 00:02:05.046 A:middle
on them while they work out.

00:02:06.026 --> 00:02:07.156 A:middle
Being untethered from the Mac

00:02:07.156 --> 00:02:08.556 A:middle
will make this much easier as

00:02:08.556 --> 00:02:08.996 A:middle
well.

00:02:09.596 --> 00:02:12.956 A:middle
For those of you building apps

00:02:12.956 --> 00:02:15.276 A:middle
for accessories, I'm happy to

00:02:15.276 --> 00:02:16.686 A:middle
tell you that you are finally

00:02:16.736 --> 00:02:17.826 A:middle
able to debug your app on the

00:02:17.826 --> 00:02:17.976 A:middle
device

00:02:18.106 --> 00:02:20.016 A:middle
while the accessory's plugged in

00:02:20.016 --> 00:02:21.776 A:middle
to the Lightning port.

00:02:22.516 --> 00:02:24.636 A:middle
[ Applause ]

00:02:25.136 --> 00:02:26.296 A:middle
We think accessory makers are

00:02:26.296 --> 00:02:27.276 A:middle
going to love wireless

00:02:27.276 --> 00:02:27.876 A:middle
development.

00:02:29.226 --> 00:02:30.186 A:middle
And for the rest of us

00:02:30.546 --> 00:02:31.976 A:middle
convenience will be a big factor

00:02:32.326 --> 00:02:34.496 A:middle
in choosing when to go wireless.

00:02:34.746 --> 00:02:35.986 A:middle
We don't always remember to

00:02:35.986 --> 00:02:37.686 A:middle
bring our cables with us or

00:02:37.686 --> 00:02:38.776 A:middle
sometimes the Lightning port is

00:02:38.776 --> 00:02:40.236 A:middle
in use for some other purpose.

00:02:40.756 --> 00:02:42.146 A:middle
But now, just having the option

00:02:42.146 --> 00:02:44.096 A:middle
to jump on a Wi-Fi network to

00:02:44.096 --> 00:02:45.396 A:middle
continue developing and

00:02:45.396 --> 00:02:47.136 A:middle
debugging on our device, will be

00:02:47.136 --> 00:02:48.246 A:middle
a huge convenience.

00:02:48.776 --> 00:02:50.936 A:middle
Now, it's not only iOS

00:02:50.976 --> 00:02:53.266 A:middle
developers who can enjoy this

00:02:53.266 --> 00:02:53.906 A:middle
convenience.

00:02:54.846 --> 00:02:56.266 A:middle
Wirelessly connected Apple TVs

00:02:56.266 --> 00:02:56.976 A:middle
are also supported.

00:02:57.516 --> 00:03:02.546 A:middle
[ Applause ]

00:03:03.046 --> 00:03:04.566 A:middle
So now Apple TV developers can

00:03:04.566 --> 00:03:05.916 A:middle
develop and debug on their Apple

00:03:05.916 --> 00:03:08.166 A:middle
TVs over Wi-Fi.

00:03:08.456 --> 00:03:10.256 A:middle
Apple TV developers, your living

00:03:10.256 --> 00:03:11.836 A:middle
room is now your development

00:03:11.836 --> 00:03:12.306 A:middle
studio.

00:03:12.736 --> 00:03:14.676 A:middle
Sit back and relax on your couch

00:03:14.906 --> 00:03:16.476 A:middle
while you build the next great

00:03:16.476 --> 00:03:16.976 A:middle
Apple TV game

00:03:17.016 --> 00:03:18.161 A:middle
[ Applause ]

00:03:18.161 --> 00:03:19.306 A:middle
.

00:03:19.306 --> 00:03:20.486 A:middle
There's no need to stretch

00:03:20.486 --> 00:03:22.246 A:middle
cables across the room, to trip

00:03:22.246 --> 00:03:24.506 A:middle
over your kids or roommates or

00:03:24.506 --> 00:03:25.156 A:middle
dogs or cats.

00:03:25.596 --> 00:03:26.916 A:middle
We think Apple TV developers are

00:03:26.916 --> 00:03:28.046 A:middle
going to love wireless

00:03:28.046 --> 00:03:29.536 A:middle
development, and we can't wait

00:03:29.536 --> 00:03:31.486 A:middle
to see the next great Apple TV

00:03:31.486 --> 00:03:32.306 A:middle
game that you build while

00:03:32.306 --> 00:03:32.976 A:middle
relaxing in your living room.

00:03:40.236 --> 00:03:41.486 A:middle
So what do you need to be able

00:03:41.486 --> 00:03:42.796 A:middle
to take advantage of wireless

00:03:42.796 --> 00:03:43.366 A:middle
development?

00:03:44.156 --> 00:03:45.206 A:middle
Well, you just need an iPhone,

00:03:45.206 --> 00:03:47.706 A:middle
iPad or iPod touch, running iOS

00:03:47.706 --> 00:03:49.986 A:middle
11 or an Apple TV running tvOS

00:03:49.986 --> 00:03:50.526 A:middle
11.

00:03:50.526 --> 00:03:52.736 A:middle
And on the Mac you just need to

00:03:52.736 --> 00:03:56.656 A:middle
be running macOS 10.12.4 or

00:03:56.836 --> 00:03:56.976 A:middle
later.

00:03:57.056 --> 00:03:58.016 A:middle
What about tools support?

00:03:59.126 --> 00:04:00.656 A:middle
Well, Xcode has extensive

00:04:00.656 --> 00:04:02.256 A:middle
support for wirelessly connected

00:04:02.256 --> 00:04:02.816 A:middle
devices.

00:04:03.206 --> 00:04:04.446 A:middle
In fact, Xcode treats a

00:04:04.446 --> 00:04:06.246 A:middle
wirelessly connected device in

00:04:06.246 --> 00:04:07.816 A:middle
exactly the same way as a USB

00:04:07.816 --> 00:04:09.496 A:middle
connected device, so all of the

00:04:09.496 --> 00:04:11.036 A:middle
device actions will just work,

00:04:11.666 --> 00:04:13.036 A:middle
installing and running your app

00:04:13.036 --> 00:04:14.256 A:middle
on the device, of course, as

00:04:14.256 --> 00:04:15.666 A:middle
well as debugging your app, and

00:04:15.856 --> 00:04:16.986 A:middle
this includes all of the

00:04:16.986 --> 00:04:18.656 A:middle
advanced debugging features,

00:04:18.656 --> 00:04:19.866 A:middle
such as V debugging, Memory

00:04:19.866 --> 00:04:21.346 A:middle
Graph debugging and GP Frame

00:04:21.346 --> 00:04:21.706 A:middle
debugging.

00:04:22.836 --> 00:04:24.316 A:middle
Profiling in instruments works

00:04:24.316 --> 00:04:26.126 A:middle
great as well, and other tools

00:04:26.126 --> 00:04:27.596 A:middle
that also support wirelessly

00:04:27.596 --> 00:04:29.036 A:middle
connected devices, include

00:04:29.036 --> 00:04:31.206 A:middle
Accessibility Inspector, Console

00:04:31.206 --> 00:04:32.356 A:middle
and Configurator.

00:04:32.586 --> 00:04:38.046 A:middle
For tvOS developers, Safari Web

00:04:38.046 --> 00:04:40.366 A:middle
Inspector supports wirelessly

00:04:40.366 --> 00:04:41.476 A:middle
connected Apple TVs.

00:04:41.826 --> 00:04:43.396 A:middle
So this is great news for

00:04:43.396 --> 00:04:44.446 A:middle
TVMLKit developers.

00:04:44.856 --> 00:04:46.096 A:middle
And QuickTime screen recording

00:04:46.096 --> 00:04:48.256 A:middle
also supports wirelessly

00:04:48.256 --> 00:04:51.246 A:middle
connected Apple TVs.

00:04:51.436 --> 00:04:52.286 A:middle
Now, while we're calling this

00:04:52.286 --> 00:04:53.696 A:middle
wireless development, strictly

00:04:53.696 --> 00:04:55.506 A:middle
speaking, you're not limited to

00:04:55.506 --> 00:04:56.666 A:middle
only connecting your devices

00:04:56.666 --> 00:04:57.256 A:middle
over Wi-Fi.

00:04:57.436 --> 00:04:59.436 A:middle
While Wi-Fi will be a popular

00:04:59.436 --> 00:05:01.956 A:middle
choice, for those of us that

00:05:01.956 --> 00:05:03.316 A:middle
support it, Ethernet will work

00:05:03.316 --> 00:05:04.156 A:middle
great as well.

00:05:04.666 --> 00:05:06.476 A:middle
Really, any combination of Wi-Fi

00:05:06.476 --> 00:05:08.056 A:middle
and Ethernet to connect your

00:05:08.056 --> 00:05:09.006 A:middle
device and your Mac over the

00:05:09.006 --> 00:05:11.216 A:middle
network works great, provided

00:05:11.216 --> 00:05:12.536 A:middle
that your Mac and your device

00:05:12.536 --> 00:05:14.626 A:middle
can connect to each other over

00:05:14.626 --> 00:05:15.806 A:middle
that network.

00:05:18.656 --> 00:05:20.916 A:middle
And just to be clear, the option

00:05:20.916 --> 00:05:22.366 A:middle
to connect your devices over USB

00:05:22.676 --> 00:05:24.276 A:middle
remains as it always has been.

00:05:24.496 --> 00:05:25.436 A:middle
So these are now all your

00:05:25.436 --> 00:05:27.306 A:middle
options for connecting your

00:05:27.306 --> 00:05:29.266 A:middle
devices with your development

00:05:29.266 --> 00:05:29.626 A:middle
tools.

00:05:30.176 --> 00:05:33.106 A:middle
So that's just been a brief

00:05:33.156 --> 00:05:34.586 A:middle
introduction to wireless

00:05:34.586 --> 00:05:35.136 A:middle
development.

00:05:35.256 --> 00:05:36.816 A:middle
And now, to give you details on

00:05:36.816 --> 00:05:38.246 A:middle
how to pair your devices and to

00:05:38.246 --> 00:05:39.286 A:middle
talk about the workflow, I'd

00:05:39.286 --> 00:05:39.916 A:middle
like to invite up Breckin.

00:05:40.516 --> 00:05:46.606 A:middle
[ Applause ]

00:05:47.106 --> 00:05:49.816 A:middle
&gt;&gt; Thanks, Chris.

00:05:49.866 --> 00:05:50.336 A:middle
All right.

00:05:50.386 --> 00:05:52.166 A:middle
Well, we've been working really

00:05:52.166 --> 00:05:53.876 A:middle
hard on wireless development for

00:05:53.876 --> 00:05:56.366 A:middle
Xcode 9, and I can't wait to

00:05:56.366 --> 00:05:58.586 A:middle
talk about it with you, so let's

00:05:58.586 --> 00:05:59.176 A:middle
get started.

00:06:00.286 --> 00:06:01.676 A:middle
How do you set up your device

00:06:01.806 --> 00:06:03.016 A:middle
for wireless development?

00:06:03.626 --> 00:06:05.066 A:middle
Well, it's really easy.

00:06:05.816 --> 00:06:07.436 A:middle
Just go to the Devices and

00:06:07.436 --> 00:06:09.816 A:middle
Simulators window and connect

00:06:09.816 --> 00:06:12.396 A:middle
your device to your Mac with

00:06:12.396 --> 00:06:13.576 A:middle
your Lightning or USB cable.

00:06:14.556 --> 00:06:15.626 A:middle
The device will show up, as it

00:06:15.626 --> 00:06:16.386 A:middle
always has, but you'll notice

00:06:16.386 --> 00:06:16.956 A:middle
there's a new option.

00:06:22.046 --> 00:06:23.256 A:middle
Connect via network.

00:06:24.246 --> 00:06:26.776 A:middle
Just enable this option and if

00:06:26.776 --> 00:06:28.566 A:middle
the device and the Mac are on

00:06:28.566 --> 00:06:30.486 A:middle
the same network, after a few

00:06:30.486 --> 00:06:32.316 A:middle
moments you'll see a globe icon

00:06:32.316 --> 00:06:32.826 A:middle
appear to the right of the

00:06:32.826 --> 00:06:32.976 A:middle
device.

00:06:37.226 --> 00:06:38.906 A:middle
Once this globe icon appears,

00:06:38.996 --> 00:06:40.596 A:middle
you know you can unplug your

00:06:40.596 --> 00:06:42.256 A:middle
cable and continue developing

00:06:42.256 --> 00:06:43.666 A:middle
your app completely wirelessly.

00:06:44.166 --> 00:06:46.346 A:middle
Now, this works identically for

00:06:46.346 --> 00:06:48.366 A:middle
iPhone, iPad, iPod touch and

00:06:48.366 --> 00:06:51.396 A:middle
Apple TV, but for Apple TV

00:06:52.566 --> 00:06:53.426 A:middle
there's something else.

00:06:54.166 --> 00:06:56.556 A:middle
So as Chris mentioned, a lot of

00:06:56.556 --> 00:06:58.266 A:middle
our Apple TVs, they're not

00:06:58.266 --> 00:06:59.766 A:middle
sitting on our desks, they're in

00:06:59.766 --> 00:07:01.116 A:middle
our entertainment center and,

00:07:01.206 --> 00:07:02.516 A:middle
you know, you've got your cables

00:07:02.516 --> 00:07:03.496 A:middle
set up just the way you want

00:07:03.496 --> 00:07:04.946 A:middle
them, all of that.

00:07:04.946 --> 00:07:05.976 A:middle
The last thing you want to do is

00:07:05.976 --> 00:07:07.146 A:middle
reach back there and unplug

00:07:07.146 --> 00:07:08.866 A:middle
everything and connect a USB-C

00:07:08.866 --> 00:07:11.846 A:middle
cable, so luckily for Apple TV,

00:07:11.986 --> 00:07:12.806 A:middle
you don't have to do that.

00:07:12.906 --> 00:07:14.386 A:middle
We support wireless pairing in

00:07:14.386 --> 00:07:17.336 A:middle
Discovery, so to do that all you

00:07:17.336 --> 00:07:18.966 A:middle
have to do is go to the Remote

00:07:18.966 --> 00:07:21.146 A:middle
App and Devices screen on your

00:07:21.146 --> 00:07:21.726 A:middle
Apple TV.

00:07:23.006 --> 00:07:24.866 A:middle
Once you go there, go back to

00:07:24.866 --> 00:07:25.976 A:middle
the Devices and Simulators

00:07:25.976 --> 00:07:26.826 A:middle
window in Xcode.

00:07:27.326 --> 00:07:29.276 A:middle
That Apple TV will appear as a

00:07:29.276 --> 00:07:31.096 A:middle
discovered device automatically.

00:07:31.706 --> 00:07:33.626 A:middle
Once you select that device, a

00:07:33.626 --> 00:07:34.666 A:middle
pin code will appear on your

00:07:34.666 --> 00:07:35.186 A:middle
Apple TV.

00:07:35.706 --> 00:07:37.696 A:middle
Just put that pin code in and

00:07:38.926 --> 00:07:39.906 A:middle
click Connect.

00:07:41.096 --> 00:07:43.546 A:middle
After you connect it will be the

00:07:43.546 --> 00:07:45.246 A:middle
same as if you had paired with

00:07:45.246 --> 00:07:47.316 A:middle
it via USB-C cable.

00:07:47.806 --> 00:07:49.206 A:middle
We think this is great for Apple

00:07:49.276 --> 00:07:50.846 A:middle
TV development.

00:07:52.636 --> 00:07:53.236 A:middle
All right.

00:07:53.236 --> 00:07:56.476 A:middle
So that's getting paired, but I

00:07:56.476 --> 00:07:57.536 A:middle
know some of you are wondering,

00:07:57.716 --> 00:07:58.846 A:middle
you know, is it really that easy

00:07:58.846 --> 00:08:01.746 A:middle
to connect, and the answer for

00:08:01.746 --> 00:08:04.176 A:middle
almost everyone is absolutely.

00:08:04.546 --> 00:08:07.936 A:middle
So for most home and small

00:08:07.936 --> 00:08:09.306 A:middle
business networks no

00:08:09.306 --> 00:08:10.566 A:middle
configuration is necessary.

00:08:10.796 --> 00:08:12.176 A:middle
Just make sure that your Mac and

00:08:12.176 --> 00:08:13.186 A:middle
your devices are on the same

00:08:13.186 --> 00:08:14.226 A:middle
network and everything just

00:08:14.226 --> 00:08:14.466 A:middle
works.

00:08:15.396 --> 00:08:18.466 A:middle
Now, we know some of you work on

00:08:18.466 --> 00:08:20.036 A:middle
more complex networks, say

00:08:20.036 --> 00:08:21.736 A:middle
corporate, large institutional

00:08:21.736 --> 00:08:23.626 A:middle
networks, and if your system

00:08:23.626 --> 00:08:26.126 A:middle
administrator has set up certain

00:08:26.296 --> 00:08:27.806 A:middle
restrictions, it may be a little

00:08:27.806 --> 00:08:29.506 A:middle
more difficult, but not by much

00:08:29.506 --> 00:08:30.726 A:middle
because we now support

00:08:30.896 --> 00:08:32.226 A:middle
connecting directly by IP

00:08:32.226 --> 00:08:34.666 A:middle
address to your device.

00:08:35.696 --> 00:08:36.626 A:middle
This is really easy.

00:08:37.036 --> 00:08:38.876 A:middle
Not quite as easy as doing

00:08:38.876 --> 00:08:40.776 A:middle
nothing, but all you have to do

00:08:40.776 --> 00:08:42.286 A:middle
is Control click on the device

00:08:42.286 --> 00:08:43.346 A:middle
in the Devices and Simulators

00:08:43.346 --> 00:08:46.686 A:middle
window and you'll see a Connect

00:08:46.686 --> 00:08:47.636 A:middle
via IP address option.

00:08:47.846 --> 00:08:51.716 A:middle
Just click that and then go to

00:08:51.716 --> 00:08:52.956 A:middle
your settings on your device,

00:08:53.296 --> 00:08:54.836 A:middle
get your IP address, enter it in

00:08:54.836 --> 00:08:55.666 A:middle
and you can connect.

00:08:55.946 --> 00:08:58.736 A:middle
So adds a little bit of a

00:08:58.736 --> 00:08:59.626 A:middle
technical aside.

00:09:00.306 --> 00:09:01.846 A:middle
If you can ping the device from

00:09:01.846 --> 00:09:03.826 A:middle
the Mac, you're probably good to

00:09:03.826 --> 00:09:04.106 A:middle
go.

00:09:04.306 --> 00:09:06.836 A:middle
Now, if you want any of the

00:09:06.836 --> 00:09:08.566 A:middle
deeper details as far as ports,

00:09:08.756 --> 00:09:09.646 A:middle
maybe to pass to your system

00:09:09.646 --> 00:09:11.226 A:middle
administrator, please check out

00:09:11.226 --> 00:09:12.166 A:middle
the wireless development

00:09:12.166 --> 00:09:12.936 A:middle
documentation.

